title: Uttarakhand elections: CM Harish Rawat releases Congress manifesto in Dehradun
text:
Uttarakhand elections: CM Harish Rawat releases Congress manifesto in Dehradun Uttarakhand elections: CM Harish Rawat releases Congress manifesto in Dehradun All parties' heavyweights are gearing up for their rallies, with the heat for election campaign in Uttarakhand is rising. Senior leaders of BJP and Congress would hold rallies as well as road shows in various districts of the state today. By: FE Online | Dehradun | Updated: February 5, 2017 1:51 PM Congress party released its manifesto for Uttarakhand assembly elections on Sunday. (ANI) 
Uttarakhand elections: Congress party released its manifesto for Uttarakhand assembly elections on Sunday. Chief Minister Harish Rawat along with other members released the manifesto in Dehradun. It is a power packed day for Uttarakhand elections on Sunday, Congress leader Ambika Soni and CM Rawat would also address public rallies in various parts of the state. BJP leader and Union Home Minister Rajnath Singh will be seen addressing rallies in Pithoragarh and Haridwar districts while Finance Minister Arun Jaitley is to visit parts of Nainital district. Bahujan Samaj Party Supremo Mayawati will address an election rally in Uttarakhand’s Sitarganj.
